1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,325 --> 00:01:38,165
=Episode 9=

3
00:01:39,180 --> 00:01:41,130
Are you alone at home now?

4
00:01:41,330 --> 00:01:42,570
Is anyone else at home with you?

5
00:01:43,290 --> 00:01:44,850
No. I'm alone.

6
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:46,570
Sure. Just wait there.

7
00:01:46,740 --> 00:01:48,180
I'll get a ride immediately

8
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:49,290
and go to your house.

9
00:01:49,740 --> 00:01:50,980
Don't come to my house.

10
00:01:51,210 --> 00:01:54,020
My house is a mess now.

11
00:01:54,133 --> 00:01:56,170
Don't worry.
I always visit my client's house.

12
00:01:56,180 --> 00:01:57,290
I've seen all kinds of mess.

13
00:01:57,290 --> 00:01:58,290
I'm fine with any mess.

14
00:01:58,466 --> 00:01:59,290
If you don't mind,

15
00:01:59,290 --> 00:02:00,866
I can even help you clean up the mess.

16
00:02:01,850 --> 00:02:02,690
Seriously...

17
00:02:02,820 --> 00:02:03,570
Seriously...

18
00:02:03,740 --> 00:02:06,100
Why are you doing this, Ms. Qin?

19
00:02:07,410 --> 00:02:09,010
You are my lawyer.

20
00:02:09,340 --> 00:02:10,940
I am your client.

21
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:12,890
You serve me.

22
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:15,660
If I want to file a lawsuit, I file it.

23
00:02:15,730 --> 00:02:18,060
If I want to withdraw it, I withdraw it.

24
00:02:18,060 --> 00:02:20,380
Why do you have so much to say?

25
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:21,290
Fine, then.

26
00:02:21,290 --> 00:02:22,820
If you're not willing,

27
00:02:22,980 --> 00:02:24,410
I'll go talk to the judge myself.

28
00:02:24,850 --> 00:02:25,940
That works, right?

29
00:02:29,540 --> 00:02:30,380
What?

30
00:02:30,780 --> 00:02:31,890
She hung up?

31
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:34,130
Ms. Shu,

32
00:02:34,130 --> 00:02:35,850
I came today to discuss

33
00:02:35,850 --> 00:02:38,260
my client Liu Mingxi's case with you.

34
00:02:38,570 --> 00:02:39,900
She wants to withdraw the lawsuit?

35
00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:42,130
Did the parties reach
a settlement on their own?

36
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:43,690
Do you think there's a problem?

37
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:46,220
It doesn't seem quite right to me.

38
00:02:46,450 --> 00:02:47,500
From how Ms. Liu sounded,

39
00:02:47,510 --> 00:02:49,400
it didn't feel like
she was withdrawing voluntarily.

40
00:02:49,444 --> 00:02:50,711
Although there's no evidence,

41
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:52,010
that's why

42
00:02:52,660 --> 00:02:54,730
I came to talk to you,

43
00:02:55,170 --> 00:02:56,450
to see if I could submit

44
00:02:56,450 --> 00:02:57,980
the withdrawal application a bit later.

45
00:02:58,410 --> 00:02:59,100
Sure.

46
00:02:59,170 --> 00:03:00,780
But do you think you can

47
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:02,780
personally speak with her
and persuade her?

48
00:03:03,780 --> 00:03:05,820
As her lawyer,
when I try to persuade her,

49
00:03:06,570 --> 00:03:07,780
she really doesn't listen.

50
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:09,450
Have you not established

51
00:03:09,450 --> 00:03:11,311
a trusting relationship
with your client yet?

52
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:13,060
If she won't listen to you,

53
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:14,570
as a judge,

54
00:03:15,060 --> 00:03:16,500
even if I talk to her for a bit,

55
00:03:16,940 --> 00:03:18,780
it probably won't make much difference.

56
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:19,690
Yes.

57
00:03:20,060 --> 00:03:20,820
But she told me

58
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:22,570
that since we haven't signed a contract

59
00:03:22,688 --> 00:03:24,570
and haven't established
a formal relationship,

60
00:03:24,777 --> 00:03:27,311
she believes I have no right
to interfere with her decision.

61
00:03:27,450 --> 00:03:28,380
But I don't know

62
00:03:28,660 --> 00:03:30,100
who taught her to say that.

63
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:32,780
I feel like Ms. Liu...

64
00:03:32,940 --> 00:03:34,600
She isn't someone who would say that.

65
00:03:35,290 --> 00:03:36,060
Right.

66
00:03:36,170 --> 00:03:37,850
So I wanted to ask for your help

67
00:03:37,850 --> 00:03:39,850
to persuade her from your side.

68
00:03:42,570 --> 00:03:43,500
How about this?

69
00:03:43,940 --> 00:03:46,290
Before your withdrawal application
is submitted,

70
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:47,933
I'll arrange an external mediation.

71
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:48,890
If the parties can

72
00:03:48,890 --> 00:03:51,290
reach a settlement themselves,
that would be best.

73
00:03:52,060 --> 00:03:52,890
If Ms. Liu

74
00:03:52,890 --> 00:03:54,410
really has something she can't say,

75
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,500
we can't let her suffer in silence.

76
00:03:57,260 --> 00:03:58,010
Right.

77
00:03:58,260 --> 00:03:59,290
Thank you, Ms. Shu.

78
00:03:59,380 --> 00:04:01,260
With your words, I feel reassured.

79
00:04:02,170 --> 00:04:04,340
Jing, the meeting's
about to start. Let's go.

80
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:06,290
Judge Yu, hi.

81
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:07,850
Do you have anything else?

82
00:04:08,260 --> 00:04:09,890
I'm fine. You go ahead.

83
00:04:16,850 --> 00:04:17,980
What are you looking at?

84
00:04:17,980 --> 00:04:18,810
Take a look.

85
00:04:19,290 --> 00:04:21,140
I had the appraisal
department examine it.

86
00:04:21,540 --> 00:04:23,660
The old man said, "Just let me die.

87
00:04:23,660 --> 00:04:25,066
Stop putting me through this."

88
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:28,580
You're planning to hand this

89
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:30,410
to those three troublemakers?

90
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:31,850
Will they accept it?

91
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:33,700
His family

92
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:35,610
doesn't care how he dies.

93
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:38,140
They only care whether they can
extort money from each other.

94
00:04:54,290 --> 00:04:55,810
(Xiezhi. Oh, Xiezhi,)

95
00:04:56,370 --> 00:04:57,580
(the horn on your head)

96
00:04:58,170 --> 00:05:00,290
(is meant to distinguish
right from wrong,)

97
00:05:00,422 --> 00:05:02,377
(to tell good from evil,
loyalty from treachery.)

98
00:05:03,020 --> 00:05:04,490
(Now, you've gone bald, haven't you?)

99
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:09,580
(You pride yourself on justice,
judging things clearly,)

100
00:05:09,911 --> 00:05:11,980
(and not letting them
get tangled in conflict.)

101
00:05:12,497 --> 00:05:14,467
(But have I truly understood)

102
00:05:15,340 --> 00:05:17,410
(the desires behind the parties?)

103
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:20,900
(Family Court.)

104
00:05:21,730 --> 00:05:22,730
(Family matters.)

105
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:24,290
(Filial piety and harmony.)

106
00:05:25,170 --> 00:05:26,580
(How much do I really understand?)

107
00:06:01,460 --> 00:06:02,980
Judge, please enter the court.

108
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,340
Please be seated.

109
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:16,866
Court is now in session.

110
00:06:17,533 --> 00:06:19,955
(Conference Room, In Use)
Maintain a positive mindset.

111
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:22,340
Avoid anger. Stay calm.

112
00:06:22,540 --> 00:06:24,580
This is crucial

113
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,120
(Director Xie Zhuoyuan, Chief Physician)
for breast health.

114
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,020
(of the Breast Department of People's Hospital)
However,

115
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:29,460
for judges as a profession,

116
00:06:29,580 --> 00:06:31,700
this is completely unrealistic.

117
00:06:34,410 --> 00:06:35,340
Exercise more.

118
00:06:35,660 --> 00:06:37,850
Reduce excess body fat.

119
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:39,780
Prevent obesity

120
00:06:40,020 --> 00:06:41,930
from increasing breast hyperplasia.

121
00:06:42,140 --> 00:06:45,020
In this regard,
all of you are doing very well.

122
00:06:45,490 --> 00:06:47,490
From the moment
I entered the courthouse,

123
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:48,340
I haven't

124
00:06:48,340 --> 00:06:50,700
seen a single female judge

125
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:53,140
whose uniform is tight.

126
00:06:54,780 --> 00:06:56,780
Reduce estrogen levels in the body.

127
00:06:57,410 --> 00:06:59,170
Control estrogen intake.

128
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:00,490
Married women

129
00:07:00,490 --> 00:07:02,930
should maintain a harmonious sex life.

130
00:07:03,250 --> 00:07:05,133
I'm not sure about

131
00:07:05,222 --> 00:07:08,490
the marital status and emotional lives
of our female judges,

132
00:07:08,850 --> 00:07:11,370
but I do know my son
was assigned to work at the court

133
00:07:11,370 --> 00:07:12,900
after he graduated from college

134
00:07:13,580 --> 00:07:15,930
and is still single to this day.

135
00:07:16,050 --> 00:07:17,050
Same here.

136
00:07:17,050 --> 00:07:18,610
Director Xie, who is your son?

137
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:20,066
I'm considering marrying him.

138
00:07:20,090 --> 00:07:22,155
You can have the son,
and I'll take the mother-in-law.

139
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,700
Mother-in-law, I choose you.

140
00:07:23,850 --> 00:07:24,930
Do you choose me?

141
00:07:27,730 --> 00:07:30,730
There are still too few male judges
in the Family Division.

142
00:07:31,340 --> 00:07:32,900
But under pressure,

143
00:07:32,955 --> 00:07:35,200
breast health doesn't distinguish
between men and women.

144
00:07:35,311 --> 00:07:37,780
Male judges should also
take it seriously.

145
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:42,730
(Hello, everyone.)

146
00:07:42,730 --> 00:07:45,540
(Ms. Qin is here today
at the entrance of Qingcheng Court)

147
00:07:46,020 --> 00:07:47,780
(to give everyone a serious reminder.)

148
00:07:48,460 --> 00:07:50,170
(Beware of visitation agreement traps.)

149
00:07:50,290 --> 00:07:51,850
(Beware of visitation agreement traps.)

150
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:59,820
(Beware)

151
00:08:01,490 --> 00:08:02,580
(Years of marriage,)

152
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:03,777
(ending in a single moment.)

153
00:08:03,822 --> 00:08:05,200
(Every step is taken with caution)

154
00:08:05,288 --> 00:08:06,400
(and carefully calculated.)

155
00:08:06,610 --> 00:08:08,930
(All because of signing one document)

156
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:11,170
(and one small oversight...)

157
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:14,020
(Sorry.)

158
00:08:18,050 --> 00:08:19,140
(Slow down.)

159
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:21,980
(Slow down.)

160
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:00,300
(Slow down.)

161
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:02,850
(Don't rush. Take it slow.)

162
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,890
When you married your ex-wife,

163
00:09:06,890 --> 00:09:08,250
you booked fifty tables

164
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:10,100
at the Royal Palace Hotel.

165
00:09:10,610 --> 00:09:11,460
Who told you that?

166
00:09:11,460 --> 00:09:12,650
Just admit it.

167
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,800
Was it that guy Datuo who told you?

168
00:09:14,911 --> 00:09:17,130
He just doesn't want
to see me doing well.

169
00:09:17,130 --> 00:09:18,420
Plaintiff, mind your language.

170
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:21,300
You keep saying I'm the most
important person in your heart.

171
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:22,650
If you had treated me

172
00:09:22,650 --> 00:09:24,488
even half as well
as you treated your ex-wife,

173
00:09:24,580 --> 00:09:26,420
would we have ended up like this?

174
00:09:26,530 --> 00:09:29,060
Wu, is this how you want
to settle scores with me?

175
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:31,940
You insist on comparing yourself
with my ex-wife, right? Fine.

176
00:09:32,220 --> 00:09:33,420
Let me make a comparison, then.

177
00:09:33,488 --> 00:09:34,770
You've seen her photos, right?

178
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:37,100
Don't you have
any self-awareness at all?

179
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,340
She's not just good-looking,

180
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:40,530
but she's diligent and disciplined.

181
00:09:40,530 --> 00:09:40,940
And you?

182
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,820
You sleep until noon every day.
Does that even compare?

183
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:45,820
She's filial
and emotionally intelligent.

184
00:09:46,060 --> 00:09:47,490
She never makes my mother worry.

185
00:09:47,490 --> 00:09:48,710
How have you treated my mother?

186
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,370
Marrying into our family,

187
00:09:50,370 --> 00:09:51,770
you should be grateful.

188
00:09:51,770 --> 00:09:52,610
You jerk!

189
00:09:52,610 --> 00:09:53,250
Shut up!

190
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:54,940
Who else would even want you besides me?

191
00:09:54,940 --> 00:09:55,700
Shut up!

192
00:09:56,180 --> 00:09:58,860
(He Yuchi)

193
00:09:59,610 --> 00:10:00,530
Come in.

194
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:04,940
Shu Jing,

195
00:10:05,130 --> 00:10:06,060
you're just in time.

196
00:10:06,130 --> 00:10:07,980
The forensic report
from Mingjing has arrived.

197
00:10:08,180 --> 00:10:09,100
What does it say?

198
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:11,700
Internal organ congestion and swelling.

199
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:13,250
(Cause of death)
Significant bleeding

200
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:14,777
in the cardiopulmonary serosa.
Clear signs of cyanosis.

201
00:10:14,844 --> 00:10:16,400
Cause of death is hypoxia at the scene.

202
00:10:16,850 --> 00:10:17,770
Take a look.

203
00:10:19,180 --> 00:10:20,060
Also,

204
00:10:20,130 --> 00:10:21,060
the trace analysis team

205
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:23,220
found two fingerprints
on the oxygen tube.

206
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:25,940
Based on the direction
and pressure of the prints,

207
00:10:26,220 --> 00:10:27,010
it can be confirmed

208
00:10:27,010 --> 00:10:28,822
that the elderly man
removed the tube himself.

209
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:30,060
In other words,

210
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:31,370
this was suicide.

211
00:10:33,610 --> 00:10:34,370
However,

212
00:10:34,370 --> 00:10:36,100
even though we now
have forensic evidence

213
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,340
proving Shen Xiezhi's innocence,

214
00:10:38,730 --> 00:10:41,100
we still need to stabilize
the family's emotions.

215
00:10:41,180 --> 00:10:42,577
They'll have difficulty accepting

216
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,311
the conclusion
that he took his own life.

217
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:57,940
This is...

218
00:11:01,730 --> 00:11:03,340
Ms. Shu! Judge Yu!

219
00:11:03,650 --> 00:11:04,650
I have evidence here.

220
00:11:08,650 --> 00:11:09,700
This is the video

221
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:11,244
of the elderly man removing the tube.

222
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:20,620
(Meeting Room)

223
00:11:46,140 --> 00:11:54,900
(Qingcheng Court Hearing Schedule)

224
00:12:06,580 --> 00:12:07,370
Miss,

225
00:12:07,850 --> 00:12:08,980
may I ask you something?

226
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:11,220
There's a young male judge here

227
00:12:11,580 --> 00:12:12,770
named Shen Xiezhi.

228
00:12:13,370 --> 00:12:14,850
He doesn't have a hearing today.

229
00:12:14,980 --> 00:12:16,650
Where is his office?

230
00:12:17,220 --> 00:12:18,220
You are?

231
00:12:19,444 --> 00:12:21,470
I'm the doctor who gave
the breast health lecture.

232
00:12:22,060 --> 00:12:25,940
I wanted to consult Judge Shen
about some legal matters.

233
00:12:26,010 --> 00:12:27,490
You're Director Xie, right?

234
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:29,060
Yes.

235
00:12:29,266 --> 00:12:30,644
Actually, if you have questions,

236
00:12:30,688 --> 00:12:31,822
you can ask other judges.

237
00:12:31,911 --> 00:12:33,177
Judge Shen is on leave.

238
00:12:33,490 --> 00:12:34,300
He...

239
00:12:34,820 --> 00:12:35,850
He's on leave.

240
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:39,650
Alright.

241
00:12:39,650 --> 00:12:41,300
Director Xie, anything else?

242
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:42,490
No, that's all.

243
00:12:42,650 --> 00:12:43,580
Thank you.

244
00:13:01,620 --> 00:13:03,260
(Mom)

245
00:13:03,980 --> 00:13:04,850
I'm at work.

246
00:13:04,888 --> 00:13:06,422
If there's nothing else, I'm hanging up.

247
00:13:06,466 --> 00:13:08,820
I'm at the Qingcheng Family Court.

248
00:13:09,010 --> 00:13:10,250
Where are you working?

249
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:11,340
(Qingcheng District People's Court,
Tianhai City)

250
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:12,530
Are you divorcing Dad?

251
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:14,622
Focus on your own matters.

252
00:13:16,355 --> 00:13:18,644
I'm out on external mediation.
I'm not at the courthouse.

253
00:13:18,730 --> 00:13:19,730
Shen Xiezhi,

254
00:13:20,296 --> 00:13:21,460
I've told you this.

255
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:23,250
I am a doctor.

256
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:25,911
We hate it
when patients hide their condition.

257
00:13:26,530 --> 00:13:28,580
I'm heading to your place now.

258
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:30,180
I'm not at home. Don't come.

259
00:13:30,850 --> 00:13:32,610
Fine. You're not home?

260
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:34,220
I'll play the good mother

261
00:13:34,370 --> 00:13:35,890
and go clean up for you.

262
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,420
I'm really not at home. I'm not lying.

263
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:44,300
It's just that

264
00:13:45,420 --> 00:13:46,850
something happened during a hearing.

265
00:13:47,066 --> 00:13:48,333
The family got emotional

266
00:13:48,377 --> 00:13:50,170
and caused a disturbance
at the courthouse.

267
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:52,010
The court asked me
to step aside for now.

268
00:13:52,010 --> 00:13:53,300
How serious was it?

269
00:13:54,010 --> 00:13:56,130
How upset were they?

270
00:13:57,820 --> 00:13:59,890
This involves case details.
I can't disclose it.

271
00:14:00,180 --> 00:14:01,220
Don't ask.

272
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:04,650
You didn't pick up any real skills
from your father,

273
00:14:04,850 --> 00:14:06,250
but you learned quickly

274
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:07,490
how to brush me off.

275
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:09,340
Mom, this really is...

276
00:14:09,340 --> 00:14:10,530
Then, tell me

277
00:14:10,530 --> 00:14:12,100
what exactly is going on, at least.

278
00:14:13,130 --> 00:14:14,650
All of you!

279
00:14:15,010 --> 00:14:16,850
The father, the son,

280
00:14:16,911 --> 00:14:18,422
and even the grandfather keep secrets.

281
00:14:18,610 --> 00:14:20,460
What is this, some classified bureau?

282
00:14:20,580 --> 00:14:21,460
No matter what,

283
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:23,600
you must give me a clear answer today.

284
00:14:23,955 --> 00:14:25,530
Before the investigation results
are out,

285
00:14:25,530 --> 00:14:26,955
I don't have a clear answer either.

286
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:27,940
I'm hanging up.

287
00:14:28,820 --> 00:14:29,770
Shen Xiezhi...

288
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:31,730
Son! You...

289
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:42,100
Madam,

290
00:14:42,940 --> 00:14:45,940
are you Judge Shen Xiezhi's mother?

291
00:14:46,850 --> 00:14:47,820
You are?

292
00:14:49,220 --> 00:14:50,250
Can you tell?

293
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:52,370
Things in our division
are quite serious.

294
00:14:52,730 --> 00:14:54,130
Otherwise, how could we invite

295
00:14:54,130 --> 00:14:55,850
such a top-level expert
to give a lecture?

296
00:14:55,850 --> 00:14:56,650
Exactly.

297
00:14:57,010 --> 00:14:57,730
Let me tell you,

298
00:14:57,730 --> 00:14:59,100
I just looked it up online.

299
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:01,060
For someone at Director Xie's level,

300
00:15:01,180 --> 00:15:02,650
a special consultation costs 300 yuan,

301
00:15:02,650 --> 00:15:04,222
but you still can't get an appointment.

302
00:15:04,266 --> 00:15:04,850
Really?

303
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:07,420
Where is Director Xie?

304
00:15:07,420 --> 00:15:09,300
- Mr. Ying, she's gone.
- Mr. Ying.

305
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:10,180
She just left.

306
00:15:10,622 --> 00:15:11,940
Looks like I missed her again.

307
00:15:12,130 --> 00:15:13,180
It's fine.

308
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:15,940
Judge Shen's matter has been resolved.

309
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:17,250
He was wrongfully accused.

310
00:15:17,460 --> 00:15:19,460
Can you tell me more about it?

311
00:15:19,610 --> 00:15:21,220
I don't know all the details,

312
00:15:21,220 --> 00:15:23,730
but Ms. Shu handled most of it.

313
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:26,420
She cared a lot about this case

314
00:15:26,488 --> 00:15:28,111
and came up with quite a few solutions.

315
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:30,180
Then, I'll have to

316
00:15:30,180 --> 00:15:31,490
properly thank Ms. Shu later.

317
00:15:32,060 --> 00:15:34,650
Things like this are hard to avoid,

318
00:15:34,777 --> 00:15:36,200
but we can't let them slide either.

319
00:15:36,266 --> 00:15:38,250
Let's believe in Judge Shen.

320
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:39,250
Yes.

321
00:15:39,420 --> 00:15:40,820
That puts my mind at ease.

322
00:15:41,474 --> 00:15:42,444
My son

323
00:15:42,488 --> 00:15:44,200
always shares the good
and hides the bad.

324
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:46,730
Why didn't I see you at the lecture?

325
00:15:47,340 --> 00:15:48,980
Are you a judge in the Family Court?

326
00:15:49,940 --> 00:15:50,890
No.

327
00:15:51,044 --> 00:15:53,333
The bar exam is too difficult.
I couldn't pass it.

328
00:15:53,490 --> 00:15:54,820
Then, are you a court clerk?

329
00:15:55,355 --> 00:15:57,340
Would it be fine
if I add you on WeChat?

330
00:15:58,770 --> 00:15:59,980
I don't mean anything else.

331
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:02,850
I just feel like we get along well.

332
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:07,130
Sure, I'll add you.

333
00:16:07,610 --> 00:16:08,580
All right, go ahead.

334
00:16:09,066 --> 00:16:10,311
Then, I'll scan your QR code.

335
00:16:10,355 --> 00:16:11,100
Okay, go ahead.

336
00:16:11,370 --> 00:16:12,220
Here you go.

337
00:16:13,220 --> 00:16:14,460
We understand the situation.

338
00:16:14,577 --> 00:16:16,770
Be more mindful of your approach at work
in the future.

339
00:16:16,770 --> 00:16:17,460
All right.

340
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:18,490
Going forward,

341
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,890
our division will also try
to avoid similar situations.

342
00:16:21,060 --> 00:16:23,300
We will make
appropriate arrangements afterward.

343
00:16:24,820 --> 00:16:26,340
Then, I'll inform him shortly.

344
00:16:29,490 --> 00:16:30,890
Shen is back as well.

345
00:16:30,890 --> 00:16:33,590
It's rare for everyone in our
Family Court to be gathered like this.

346
00:16:38,377 --> 00:16:40,340
Are you buying clothes
to compensate someone?

347
00:16:40,340 --> 00:16:41,890
What price range are you considering?

348
00:16:41,890 --> 00:16:43,333
I can help recommend something.

349
00:16:43,355 --> 00:16:44,355
What color does she like?

350
00:16:44,422 --> 00:16:45,610
What does she do?

351
00:16:47,010 --> 00:16:48,100
She's a lawyer.

352
00:16:48,460 --> 00:16:50,060
A lawyer? That's impressive.

353
00:16:50,340 --> 00:16:52,300
Take a look at these styles.

354
00:16:52,420 --> 00:16:54,770
They all have
a professional, confident look.

355
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:56,220
What size does she wear?

356
00:16:57,180 --> 00:16:58,300
She wears...

357
00:16:58,460 --> 00:17:00,010
Just tell me her height and weight.

358
00:17:05,220 --> 00:17:06,700
(Master)

359
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:07,460
Sorry.

360
00:17:07,620 --> 00:17:08,220
It's fine.

361
00:17:08,230 --> 00:17:09,180
I'll take this call first.

362
00:17:09,180 --> 00:17:10,010
Sure.

363
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:13,140
Hello, Ms. Shu.

364
00:17:13,180 --> 00:17:14,330
Your leave is over.

365
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:15,570
Come back to work tomorrow.

366
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:18,290
Ms. Shu, thank you for helping me.

367
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,644
Before the investigation results
are out,

368
00:17:20,810 --> 00:17:23,022
it's better that I don't
cause trouble for the court.

369
00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:25,770
You don't need to thank me for that.

370
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:28,420
The forensic side
has already found the evidence.

371
00:17:28,511 --> 00:17:31,140
Ms. Qin recorded a video
of the elderly man attempting suicide.

372
00:17:31,140 --> 00:17:32,377
It has already been submitted.

373
00:17:32,570 --> 00:17:33,530
Ms. Qin?

374
00:17:33,777 --> 00:17:36,810
Yes. She captured it unintentionally
while filming content for her account.

375
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:38,220
The footage is very clear.

376
00:17:38,968 --> 00:17:41,250
You should thank her properly later.

377
00:17:42,180 --> 00:17:42,940
All right.

378
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,160
We just finished a meeting
with the investigation team.

379
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:46,570
You can return tomorrow.

380
00:17:48,010 --> 00:17:49,010
That soon?

381
00:17:50,330 --> 00:17:52,730
Didn't the family request compensation?

382
00:17:53,220 --> 00:17:55,290
They've been insisting on that
all along.

383
00:17:55,420 --> 00:17:57,380
As long as it happened under your watch,

384
00:17:57,460 --> 00:17:59,088
they expect you to take responsibility.

385
00:17:59,460 --> 00:18:01,530
But this is a court. We follow the law.

386
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:03,088
If we agreed to compensation,

387
00:18:03,133 --> 00:18:04,460
we would be encouraging the idea

388
00:18:04,533 --> 00:18:06,940
that whoever makes the biggest scene
gets what they want.

389
00:18:07,822 --> 00:18:09,900
You don't need
to handle the compensation issue.

390
00:18:10,010 --> 00:18:11,700
Mr. He and I will take care of it.

391
00:18:12,380 --> 00:18:13,220
All right.

392
00:18:13,703 --> 00:18:14,660
Thank you, Master.

393
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,377
Take a moment to settle yourself.

394
00:18:16,422 --> 00:18:17,600
Come back to work tomorrow.

395
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:19,180
Okay.

396
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:24,180
Judge Shen,

397
00:18:24,380 --> 00:18:25,420
no matter what,

398
00:18:26,050 --> 00:18:28,050
I believe
you are not that kind of person.

399
00:18:32,380 --> 00:18:33,380
Excuse me.

400
00:18:33,719 --> 00:18:35,250
She's about

401
00:18:35,420 --> 00:18:36,380
this tall,

402
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:37,867
quite slim,

403
00:18:38,090 --> 00:18:39,140
fair-skinned,

404
00:18:39,460 --> 00:18:40,530
with an oval face.

405
00:18:41,330 --> 00:18:43,220
She's more on the cute side.

406
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:47,660
Got it.

407
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:50,090
This matter has worried you, Master.

408
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:53,010
About Xiezhi's situation,

409
00:18:53,010 --> 00:18:54,911
the court
has already issued an official notice.

410
00:18:55,140 --> 00:18:55,940
All right.

411
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:57,900
I'll pass along Master's regards.

412
00:18:58,250 --> 00:18:59,050
Goodbye.

413
00:19:02,050 --> 00:19:04,290
Drink less coffee and more tea.

414
00:19:04,420 --> 00:19:05,220
It's fine.

415
00:19:06,660 --> 00:19:07,570
Got it.

416
00:19:17,290 --> 00:19:18,180
Anything else?

417
00:19:20,980 --> 00:19:22,140
About our son,

418
00:19:22,570 --> 00:19:24,290
is there anything you want to tell me?

419
00:19:24,570 --> 00:19:25,530
No.

420
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:27,644
Something happened to our son
at the courthouse,

421
00:19:27,730 --> 00:19:28,770
and you didn't know?

422
00:19:32,490 --> 00:19:34,010
Fine, I'll tell you.

423
00:19:35,380 --> 00:19:37,290
He ran into some trouble

424
00:19:38,220 --> 00:19:39,290
with a case

425
00:19:39,810 --> 00:19:41,250
and was reported by a party.

426
00:19:41,980 --> 00:19:43,600
How did you find out about this?

427
00:19:43,688 --> 00:19:44,490
Don't ask.

428
00:19:44,810 --> 00:19:45,860
I came to see you

429
00:19:46,420 --> 00:19:48,377
because I have something
more important to ask.

430
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:51,250
You can see I'm busy with the lecture.

431
00:19:51,570 --> 00:19:52,770
Give me half an hour.

432
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:54,490
I'll be done soon, all right?

433
00:19:54,688 --> 00:19:56,733
Something happened to our son
at the court.

434
00:19:56,755 --> 00:19:57,980
Why didn't you tell me?

435
00:19:58,460 --> 00:20:00,330
I didn't mean to hide it from you.

436
00:20:00,330 --> 00:20:01,490
I just thought,

437
00:20:02,090 --> 00:20:03,860
if something went wrong

438
00:20:03,860 --> 00:20:05,530
at his workplace,

439
00:20:06,260 --> 00:20:07,533
telling you wouldn't help.

440
00:20:07,622 --> 00:20:09,660
You wouldn't be able
to do anything about it. Right?

441
00:20:09,660 --> 00:20:11,290
You'd just worry for nothing.

442
00:20:11,770 --> 00:20:12,810
Not only that,

443
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:15,530
what if you got flustered,
caused more trouble,

444
00:20:15,530 --> 00:20:16,770
and slowed things down?

445
00:20:16,770 --> 00:20:18,290
Wouldn't that make things even worse?

446
00:20:18,290 --> 00:20:20,050
What do you mean by that?

447
00:20:20,050 --> 00:20:21,250
We've been married for so long,

448
00:20:21,250 --> 00:20:22,533
and our son is already grown.

449
00:20:22,555 --> 00:20:24,160
Don't you know what kind of person I am?

450
00:20:24,620 --> 00:20:25,940
Do you think I'm someone

451
00:20:25,940 --> 00:20:27,250
who panics and makes mistakes?

452
00:20:27,730 --> 00:20:28,530
All right.

453
00:20:28,980 --> 00:20:30,530
It's all my fault, okay?

454
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,088
What exactly did you do wrong?

455
00:20:33,290 --> 00:20:34,688
From now on, if anything happens,

456
00:20:34,770 --> 00:20:36,330
I'll tell you first, all right?

457
00:20:36,330 --> 00:20:39,050
You must tell me immediately.

458
00:20:39,380 --> 00:20:40,530
Sure.

459
00:20:42,140 --> 00:20:43,730
You're not even close to our son,

460
00:20:43,888 --> 00:20:45,666
and you're not good
at comforting people.

461
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:46,940
If you told me,

462
00:20:46,940 --> 00:20:48,940
and I felt I could talk to him,

463
00:20:49,010 --> 00:20:51,290
he'd feel a bit better emotionally,
at least.

464
00:20:53,290 --> 00:20:54,420
Are you done?

465
00:20:56,860 --> 00:20:58,140
Then, how about this?

466
00:20:58,290 --> 00:20:59,730
You go handle your work first.

467
00:20:59,730 --> 00:21:01,460
I'm about to start mine.

468
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:03,660
I still have a lot to do.

469
00:21:04,140 --> 00:21:05,220
Professor Shen!

470
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:12,490
You really need to reflect on yourself.

471
00:21:14,609 --> 00:21:15,660
All right.

472
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:17,140
Go ahead, I'm listening.

473
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:20,140
Why does our son always resist you?

474
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:22,380
He's already a judge now.

475
00:21:22,420 --> 00:21:23,530
He's mature

476
00:21:23,660 --> 00:21:25,111
and capable of taking responsibility.

477
00:21:25,140 --> 00:21:27,488
You interfere in everything,
whether it's your place or not.

478
00:21:28,290 --> 00:21:28,860
That's because

479
00:21:28,860 --> 00:21:30,550
he doesn't understand
how I feel as a father.

480
00:21:30,570 --> 00:21:32,460
You watched him grow up.

481
00:21:32,730 --> 00:21:34,530
How can you have
so little confidence in him?

482
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:35,490
I'm telling you,

483
00:21:35,490 --> 00:21:36,420
you need to

484
00:21:36,490 --> 00:21:39,250
get rid of that professor attitude
at home.

485
00:21:40,290 --> 00:21:41,460
Reflect on it properly.

486
00:21:42,420 --> 00:21:43,380
All right.

487
00:21:43,660 --> 00:21:44,620
I accept that.

488
00:21:47,330 --> 00:21:48,490
So annoying.

489
00:21:50,050 --> 00:21:51,980
Are you going to
just let me reflect alone?

490
00:21:52,888 --> 00:21:54,460
When our son comes home next time,

491
00:21:54,570 --> 00:21:55,980
I'll have him reflect, too.

492
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:02,620
I'll reflect on it.

493
00:22:15,220 --> 00:22:19,580
(Jindian Law Firm)

494
00:22:27,460 --> 00:22:29,400
A judge won't take a drink
offered by a lawyer.

495
00:22:29,570 --> 00:22:30,220
From now on,

496
00:22:30,330 --> 00:22:32,730
at any time and in any setting,

497
00:22:32,730 --> 00:22:35,090
please keep a distance
of at least two meters from me.

498
00:22:35,090 --> 00:22:36,090
This is two meters.

499
00:22:36,250 --> 00:22:37,330
In the future, Judge Shen,

500
00:22:37,330 --> 00:22:39,290
please take a detour
when passing our law firm.

501
00:22:39,490 --> 00:22:41,050
If you step into our space,

502
00:22:41,050 --> 00:22:42,090
even by one millimeter

503
00:22:42,090 --> 00:22:43,577
or one centimeter, I won't forgive you.

504
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:02,666
(Judge Shen Xiezhi)
Shen Xiezhi?

505
00:23:09,220 --> 00:23:10,900
(Judge Shen Xiezhi)

506
00:23:20,580 --> 00:23:21,140
(Qin Rui)

507
00:23:21,140 --> 00:23:22,420
(Friend request)

508
00:23:39,490 --> 00:23:40,620
(I am Shen Xiezhi.)

509
00:23:41,180 --> 00:23:42,140
(Thank you very much)

510
00:23:42,290 --> 00:23:43,700
(for helping me clarify the facts.)

511
00:23:58,020 --> 00:24:02,020
(Jindian Law Firm)

512
00:24:14,180 --> 00:24:15,600
(Shen Xiezhi: I'm very sorry for)

513
00:24:15,866 --> 00:24:17,190
(staining your suit that night.)

514
00:24:17,530 --> 00:24:18,860
(I bought you a new one.)

515
00:24:18,860 --> 00:24:20,740
(It's not convenient for me
to go in right now.)

516
00:24:20,755 --> 00:24:22,133
(Can you come out to get it?)

517
00:24:22,250 --> 00:24:23,770
It's not convenient to go in?

518
00:24:36,511 --> 00:24:37,730
(Please accept my request.)

519
00:24:38,050 --> 00:24:39,980
(We can cancel out
the rearview mirror damage.)

520
00:24:40,180 --> 00:24:41,770
(I'll return the money from before)

521
00:24:41,770 --> 00:24:43,940
(Jindian Law Firm)

522
00:24:43,980 --> 00:24:45,420
(Sorry, Judge Shen.)

523
00:24:45,420 --> 00:24:47,350
(I'm outside discussing business
with a client.)

524
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:49,050
(I just saw your message.)

525
00:24:49,290 --> 00:24:51,380
(I helped you purely out of principle.)

526
00:24:51,444 --> 00:24:52,866
(I don't expect anything in return.)

527
00:24:52,911 --> 00:24:54,866
(There was absolutely
no other intention.)

528
00:25:11,090 --> 00:25:11,900
(Judge Shen,)

529
00:25:12,180 --> 00:25:14,050
(I appreciate your sincerity.)

530
00:25:14,180 --> 00:25:16,090
(But matters
should be handled separately.)

531
00:25:16,420 --> 00:25:18,980
(I will definitely return the money
for the rearview mirror.)

532
00:25:19,090 --> 00:25:20,420
(As for the clothes,)

533
00:25:20,620 --> 00:25:22,700
(that one of mine
was old and inexpensive.)

534
00:25:22,700 --> 00:25:24,120
(There's no need for you
to compensate me.)

535
00:25:24,133 --> 00:25:25,822
(You should return the new one.)

536
00:25:26,250 --> 00:25:27,570
(If you really insist,)

537
00:25:27,570 --> 00:25:30,050
(you can just cover
the dry cleaning cost.)

538
00:25:33,540 --> 00:25:36,420
(Dry Cleaning Fee)

539
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:41,900
(Transfer Note: Dry Cleaning Fee)

540
00:25:42,380 --> 00:25:43,810
(I've received the dry cleaning fee.)

541
00:25:44,220 --> 00:25:45,980
(Consider it
as me taking advantage of you.)

542
00:25:46,290 --> 00:25:47,620
(I won't accept anything else.)

543
00:25:48,050 --> 00:25:49,330
(I still have work to do.)

544
00:25:49,330 --> 00:25:51,090
(I won't be replying further for now.)

545
00:25:57,660 --> 00:25:58,900
Thank you, Ms. Qin.

546
00:25:59,000 --> 00:25:59,730
Thank you again

547
00:25:59,730 --> 00:26:01,860
for your cooperation
and support of our work.

548
00:26:02,090 --> 00:26:03,140
I'm truly grateful.

549
00:26:09,420 --> 00:26:11,540
(Jindian Law Firm)

550
00:26:30,530 --> 00:26:32,050
Why are you still awake?

551
00:26:32,050 --> 00:26:32,900
You're back?

552
00:26:33,380 --> 00:26:35,090
The doctor said
you shouldn't stay up late.

553
00:26:35,090 --> 00:26:35,770
You...

554
00:26:35,770 --> 00:26:36,730
It's fine.

555
00:26:37,250 --> 00:26:38,620
Why are you so disobedient?

556
00:26:46,940 --> 00:26:48,090
Careful, it's hot.

557
00:26:48,090 --> 00:26:49,810
What kind of soup are you making?

558
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:53,620
Did you meet Director Xie?

559
00:26:54,980 --> 00:26:57,530
No, a hearing delayed me today.

560
00:26:57,530 --> 00:26:58,311
I arrived too late.

561
00:26:58,380 --> 00:27:00,090
It's fine. We can spend a bit more

562
00:27:00,266 --> 00:27:01,620
and book her special consultation.

563
00:27:01,620 --> 00:27:03,490
Even her special appointments
are hard to get.

564
00:27:03,530 --> 00:27:05,290
Last time, the slots
were gone in a second.

565
00:27:05,290 --> 00:27:06,420
Then, let's try someone else.

566
00:27:06,620 --> 00:27:07,460
All right?

567
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:08,660
Why insist on her?

568
00:27:09,180 --> 00:27:10,180
Tianhai is huge.

569
00:27:10,460 --> 00:27:11,730
There are plenty of specialists.

570
00:27:12,770 --> 00:27:14,420
That patient Liu from last time

571
00:27:14,420 --> 00:27:15,980
recommended one.

572
00:27:15,980 --> 00:27:18,330
I forgot. I think the surname was Bai.

573
00:27:18,330 --> 00:27:19,420
Right, Bai.

574
00:27:19,620 --> 00:27:20,860
I've looked him up.

575
00:27:20,860 --> 00:27:21,940
He's very authoritative.

576
00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:23,777
His reputation
is on par with Director Xie.

577
00:27:24,490 --> 00:27:25,700
Let's book both of them.

578
00:27:25,770 --> 00:27:27,700
Whichever appointment we get first,
we'll go there.

579
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:29,380
Leave this to me. Don't worry.

580
00:27:29,380 --> 00:27:30,770
You don't need to worry about this.

581
00:27:40,330 --> 00:27:41,460
Did you receive it?

582
00:27:43,330 --> 00:27:44,660
You transferred money to me?

583
00:27:45,090 --> 00:27:46,220
Not bad.

584
00:27:46,700 --> 00:27:49,180
I'll reward you
by letting you sleep next to me tonight.

585
00:27:49,250 --> 00:27:50,140
Come on.

586
00:27:51,010 --> 00:27:53,250
Sleeping next to you is that cheap?

587
00:27:53,460 --> 00:27:53,980
Hurry up.

588
00:27:53,980 --> 00:27:55,050
Then, I'm coming.

589
00:27:55,050 --> 00:27:56,090
Come in.

590
00:28:00,730 --> 00:28:01,940
Where did you get the money?

591
00:28:02,155 --> 00:28:04,577
Shen Xiezhi transferred it to me
as a dry cleaning fee.

592
00:28:05,250 --> 00:28:07,140
Actually, he originally sent me more,

593
00:28:07,140 --> 00:28:08,444
but I didn't bother taking it.

594
00:28:09,140 --> 00:28:11,010
Impressive, really impressive.

595
00:28:11,730 --> 00:28:13,980
Madam Xue didn't know what she missed.

596
00:28:14,050 --> 00:28:15,860
We don't want her money.

597
00:28:16,290 --> 00:28:18,090
But thinking about it still hurts.

598
00:28:18,620 --> 00:28:19,700
That was a lot of money.

599
00:28:21,180 --> 00:28:22,140
It's all my fault.

600
00:28:22,290 --> 00:28:24,140
Just thinking about it
makes my heart ache.

601
00:28:26,290 --> 00:28:27,380
Don't stress out.

602
00:28:27,380 --> 00:28:28,570
Come on.

603
00:28:30,980 --> 00:28:32,010
Calm down.

604
00:28:33,010 --> 00:28:33,980
I'm going to sleep.

605
00:28:34,620 --> 00:28:36,300
(Contacts)

606
00:28:36,570 --> 00:28:38,460
Who's adding me on WeChat this late?

607
00:28:39,330 --> 00:28:40,620
Who is it? Some handsome guy?

608
00:28:41,860 --> 00:28:43,220
It really is a man.

609
00:28:45,180 --> 00:28:45,844
(Feng Shengli)

610
00:28:45,866 --> 00:28:47,140
(Feng Shengli is inviting you
to a voice call)

611
00:28:47,620 --> 00:28:48,860
He's calling me.

612
00:28:52,510 --> 00:28:53,570
Hello.

613
00:28:53,570 --> 00:28:55,980
I'm Qin Rui from Jindian Law Firm.

614
00:28:56,090 --> 00:28:57,860
What can I do for you?

615
00:28:58,090 --> 00:28:59,250
Do you remember me?

616
00:28:59,700 --> 00:29:00,420
The restroom,

617
00:29:00,660 --> 00:29:01,620
the clothing tag.

618
00:29:04,660 --> 00:29:05,730
I already told you.

619
00:29:05,900 --> 00:29:07,380
I'm not taking your case.

620
00:29:07,620 --> 00:29:08,810
You should get some rest too.

621
00:29:08,810 --> 00:29:09,960
I won't disturb you further.

622
00:29:09,980 --> 00:29:11,330
I don't think you'll refuse.

623
00:29:11,444 --> 00:29:13,010
I've sent the documents to your phone.

624
00:29:13,010 --> 00:29:13,980
Take a look.

625
00:29:21,300 --> 00:29:22,820
(Files)
Wait,

626
00:29:23,140 --> 00:29:24,770
is this some telecommunication scam?

627
00:29:25,050 --> 00:29:27,660
The materials
are already so well prepared.

628
00:29:28,730 --> 00:29:30,330
Why would he still need me in court?

629
00:29:31,250 --> 00:29:32,730
He even transferred me 2,000 yuan.

630
00:29:33,620 --> 00:29:34,330
Who is it?

631
00:29:34,530 --> 00:29:35,900
Someone I ran into today.

632
00:29:38,290 --> 00:29:38,980
Take it.

633
00:29:39,460 --> 00:29:40,770
What if he's a scammer

634
00:29:40,770 --> 00:29:42,330
and lures me to some compound?

635
00:29:43,140 --> 00:29:44,220
Forget it.

636
00:29:44,490 --> 00:29:45,860
Go to sleep.

637
00:29:49,220 --> 00:29:50,570
Go to bed, hurry.

638
00:29:53,180 --> 00:29:55,090
You have a point.
If I don't take the money,

639
00:29:55,380 --> 00:29:56,770
something's wrong with me.

640
00:30:04,530 --> 00:30:07,090
This afternoon,
Mr. He and I will meet the family.

641
00:30:07,090 --> 00:30:08,140
You don't need to attend.

642
00:30:08,244 --> 00:30:10,050
Stay out of the meeting room
this afternoon,

643
00:30:10,290 --> 00:30:11,770
so they don't see you.

644
00:30:12,810 --> 00:30:13,570
Understood.

645
00:30:13,977 --> 00:30:15,480
I don't have a hearing this afternoon.

646
00:30:15,810 --> 00:30:17,730
I'll just stay in my office.

647
00:30:17,866 --> 00:30:19,220
You've become much more mature.

648
00:30:19,330 --> 00:30:20,620
I thought you'd say

649
00:30:20,755 --> 00:30:23,377
that if you've done nothing wrong,
you have nothing to fear.

650
00:30:23,570 --> 00:30:25,250
Actually, these past few days at home,

651
00:30:26,140 --> 00:30:27,490
I've been reflecting.

652
00:30:28,140 --> 00:30:29,090
About this matter,

653
00:30:30,050 --> 00:30:31,730
I'm not completely
without responsibility.

654
00:30:32,250 --> 00:30:33,250
How so?

655
00:30:34,860 --> 00:30:36,250
I used to think a judge's role

656
00:30:36,980 --> 00:30:39,530
was to apply legal knowledge
beyond that of ordinary people

657
00:30:39,810 --> 00:30:41,180
and insight into the world

658
00:30:41,700 --> 00:30:43,380
to resolve disputes

659
00:30:43,620 --> 00:30:44,900
and uphold legal order.

660
00:30:45,570 --> 00:30:46,860
Even in the Family Court,

661
00:30:47,250 --> 00:30:49,220
I always stuck to my principles

662
00:30:49,380 --> 00:30:50,700
and never compromised.

663
00:30:50,860 --> 00:30:51,980
But Mr. Yao

664
00:30:51,980 --> 00:30:53,810
didn't need someone to punish wrongdoing

665
00:30:53,940 --> 00:30:55,700
or determine right from wrong.

666
00:30:56,180 --> 00:30:57,660
What he needed was family.

667
00:30:59,420 --> 00:31:00,900
Later, I kept thinking,

668
00:31:01,660 --> 00:31:03,010
even if they had only put on a show

669
00:31:03,010 --> 00:31:05,530
of being a loving family,

670
00:31:06,250 --> 00:31:07,860
Mr. Yao might have

671
00:31:08,490 --> 00:31:10,570
had more will to live.

672
00:31:11,530 --> 00:31:13,620
Even if they couldn't truly change

673
00:31:14,220 --> 00:31:16,330
and treat him
with care and filial respect,

674
00:31:16,770 --> 00:31:17,770
they shouldn't have...

675
00:31:21,330 --> 00:31:23,140
If, during mediation,

676
00:31:24,250 --> 00:31:25,420
I had listened more carefully

677
00:31:25,980 --> 00:31:27,490
to what each of them was saying

678
00:31:28,290 --> 00:31:29,700
and given them another chance,

679
00:31:31,050 --> 00:31:32,620
then when Mr. Yao left,

680
00:31:33,530 --> 00:31:34,900
he wouldn't have felt so hopeless.

681
00:31:36,180 --> 00:31:37,090
Perhaps

682
00:31:39,460 --> 00:31:41,290
he wouldn't have left
this world so soon.

683
00:31:45,133 --> 00:31:46,660
The fact that you can think this way

684
00:31:46,660 --> 00:31:48,530
means Judge He didn't argue
for you in vain

685
00:31:48,530 --> 00:31:49,866
in front of the investigation team

686
00:31:49,911 --> 00:31:50,940
and the family.

687
00:31:51,180 --> 00:31:52,860
He truly recognizes your abilities.

688
00:31:53,090 --> 00:31:54,490
Not your judgment in cases,

689
00:31:54,900 --> 00:31:56,250
but your ability to grow.

690
00:31:56,770 --> 00:31:58,900
See? Judge He really is impressive.

691
00:32:02,220 --> 00:32:03,090
Come in.

692
00:32:03,770 --> 00:32:05,180
Ms. Shu. Judge Shen.

693
00:32:06,940 --> 00:32:07,460
Ms. Shu,

694
00:32:07,460 --> 00:32:10,250
should we postpone
your external mediation this afternoon?

695
00:32:11,250 --> 00:32:13,250
I'm worried the meeting
with Mr. Yao's family

696
00:32:13,250 --> 00:32:14,490
may not go smoothly.

697
00:32:15,250 --> 00:32:17,290
That's possible.

698
00:32:17,730 --> 00:32:18,810
What external mediation?

699
00:32:19,010 --> 00:32:20,140
Should I go instead?

700
00:32:23,700 --> 00:32:24,490
That works.

701
00:32:28,180 --> 00:32:28,980
Ms. Liu.

702
00:32:28,980 --> 00:32:29,810
Thank you.

703
00:32:29,900 --> 00:32:32,010
Is this a portrait of you two
when you were young?

704
00:32:33,250 --> 00:32:34,220
This...

705
00:32:34,980 --> 00:32:36,220
Please, have a seat.

706
00:32:39,140 --> 00:32:40,570
This portrait

707
00:32:40,860 --> 00:32:43,620
was commissioned

708
00:32:44,490 --> 00:32:45,940
on our 30th wedding anniversary.

709
00:32:46,090 --> 00:32:47,290
Seriously,

710
00:32:47,860 --> 00:32:48,900
we agreed

711
00:32:49,090 --> 00:32:52,140
to have another one done for our 40th.

712
00:32:52,250 --> 00:32:53,660
You are not a man of your word.

713
00:33:00,940 --> 00:33:01,940
Ms. Liu,

714
00:33:02,620 --> 00:33:05,770
I've tried to speak with you
several times,

715
00:33:06,330 --> 00:33:07,940
not because I want your money,

716
00:33:08,290 --> 00:33:10,620
but because I just can't accept this.

717
00:33:10,980 --> 00:33:12,420
You told me before

718
00:33:12,533 --> 00:33:14,220
about your relationship
with your husband

719
00:33:14,490 --> 00:33:15,810
and with your children.

720
00:33:15,810 --> 00:33:17,900
You treated them so well.

721
00:33:18,250 --> 00:33:19,860
How could they treat you like this?

722
00:33:21,940 --> 00:33:24,180
Are you certain you want
to withdraw the case?

723
00:33:26,770 --> 00:33:27,770
Ms. Qin,

724
00:33:27,980 --> 00:33:29,730
please don't try to persuade me anymore.

725
00:33:30,810 --> 00:33:32,330
Now, I just feel

726
00:33:32,700 --> 00:33:34,660
I've let my husband down.

727
00:33:35,050 --> 00:33:37,010
My husband spent his whole life

728
00:33:37,570 --> 00:33:38,810
being upright

729
00:33:39,490 --> 00:33:40,860
and decent.

730
00:33:41,180 --> 00:33:42,380
What he valued most

731
00:33:42,700 --> 00:33:44,010
was his dignity.

732
00:33:44,700 --> 00:33:45,860
Look at me now,

733
00:33:46,380 --> 00:33:48,180
I've dragged things all the way
to court.

734
00:33:49,250 --> 00:33:50,250
About this...

735
00:33:51,770 --> 00:33:52,770
Let me handle this.

736
00:33:58,140 --> 00:33:59,180
Why is it you?

737
00:34:01,730 --> 00:34:03,620
I thought it would be Judge Shu Jing.

738
00:34:03,900 --> 00:34:04,980
Ms. Shu is in a meeting.

739
00:34:05,220 --> 00:34:06,180
Who is it?

740
00:34:07,730 --> 00:34:08,780
Who are you looking for?

741
00:34:08,780 --> 00:34:09,810
- Hello, Madam. - Hello.

742
00:34:09,820 --> 00:34:11,900
We're from
the Qingcheng District People's Court.

743
00:34:12,380 --> 00:34:13,420
My name is Shen Xiezhi.

744
00:34:13,860 --> 00:34:15,420
Hello, Madam. I'm Hu Aixi.

745
00:34:16,010 --> 00:34:16,820
Hello.

746
00:34:17,111 --> 00:34:19,222
Wasn't this case
already settled through mediation?

747
00:34:19,288 --> 00:34:20,844
Why is it going to a collegial panel?

748
00:34:21,570 --> 00:34:23,300
This case is

749
00:34:24,050 --> 00:34:25,050
a bit special.

750
00:34:25,530 --> 00:34:26,420
It involves

751
00:34:26,420 --> 00:34:28,820
too many sensitive issues.

752
00:34:28,820 --> 00:34:31,900
Besides, it's getting
a lot of attention online.

753
00:34:31,900 --> 00:34:34,170
This case has gone viral, you know?

754
00:34:35,010 --> 00:34:36,690
What I mean is,

755
00:34:36,980 --> 00:34:37,980
if it were just about

756
00:34:37,980 --> 00:34:40,490
mediating a family dispute,

757
00:34:40,650 --> 00:34:42,610
getting the father and son to reconcile

758
00:34:42,610 --> 00:34:44,780
would be easy for me.

759
00:34:44,780 --> 00:34:45,210
Right.

760
00:34:45,210 --> 00:34:45,940
Right?

761
00:34:45,940 --> 00:34:47,610
But now it also involves

762
00:34:48,260 --> 00:34:50,900
guiding public opinion.

763
00:34:51,010 --> 00:34:52,860
If more people

764
00:34:52,860 --> 00:34:53,911
can discuss it together,

765
00:34:53,977 --> 00:34:55,300
the case can be handled

766
00:34:55,380 --> 00:34:56,490
more thoroughly.

767
00:34:56,820 --> 00:34:58,260
After all, this case

768
00:34:58,260 --> 00:34:59,490
has drawn a lot of attention.

769
00:34:59,650 --> 00:35:01,420
We can't

770
00:35:02,010 --> 00:35:03,130
take public opinion lightly.

771
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:04,610
- Right? - That makes sense.

772
00:35:04,610 --> 00:35:05,490
And later,

773
00:35:05,490 --> 00:35:07,340
we'll have to deal with the media.

774
00:35:07,340 --> 00:35:09,650
That's definitely not my strength.

775
00:35:10,980 --> 00:35:12,460
Shu Jing is better at that.

776
00:35:12,460 --> 00:35:14,090
Yes, Ms. Shu is good at it.

777
00:35:14,170 --> 00:35:15,300
But she already has

778
00:35:15,300 --> 00:35:16,650
a heavy caseload.

779
00:35:17,460 --> 00:35:18,380
I'll ask her later.

780
00:35:18,690 --> 00:35:19,780
Sure.

781
00:35:19,780 --> 00:35:21,210
I'll check with her and see.

782
00:35:21,610 --> 00:35:22,420
Come in.

783
00:35:23,170 --> 00:35:23,820
Mr. He.

784
00:35:23,820 --> 00:35:24,940
We were just praising you.

785
00:35:24,940 --> 00:35:25,300
Shu Jing.

786
00:35:25,300 --> 00:35:26,460
Mr. Ying, you're here too?

787
00:35:26,460 --> 00:35:28,733
You came at the right time.
We were just talking about you.

788
00:35:28,740 --> 00:35:30,610
Danian has a case on elder support.

789
00:35:30,610 --> 00:35:32,311
It's getting a lot of public attention,

790
00:35:32,355 --> 00:35:33,420
and the dispute itself

791
00:35:33,420 --> 00:35:34,420
is quite unusual.

792
00:35:34,555 --> 00:35:37,530
The one where the father demands money
from his son for medical treatment

793
00:35:37,622 --> 00:35:39,266
and even pressures him
to donate a kidney?

794
00:35:39,311 --> 00:35:40,644
See? She's taking the son's side.

795
00:35:40,977 --> 00:35:42,210
I don't know the full details.

796
00:35:42,210 --> 00:35:43,570
I've only heard bits of it.

797
00:35:44,688 --> 00:35:45,977
You needed me for something?

798
00:35:46,420 --> 00:35:48,130
There's a divorce case
just assigned to me.

799
00:35:48,244 --> 00:35:50,000
The plaintiff
is my elementary school classmate.

800
00:35:50,088 --> 00:35:50,820
I request recusal.

801
00:35:50,820 --> 00:35:51,940
Elementary school classmate?

802
00:35:52,300 --> 00:35:53,090
Then...

803
00:35:53,300 --> 00:35:54,340
Danian, you take it.

804
00:35:54,466 --> 00:35:55,530
I'll follow your arrangement.

805
00:35:55,530 --> 00:35:56,900
All right, you take it then.

806
00:35:57,380 --> 00:35:59,010
Then, it's settled.

807
00:35:59,340 --> 00:36:01,860
Shu Jing,
hand over your divorce case to Danian.

808
00:36:01,860 --> 00:36:03,570
Then you, Xiezhi, and Danian

809
00:36:03,570 --> 00:36:05,340
will form a collegial panel

810
00:36:05,530 --> 00:36:07,780
to review Feng Shengli's case.

811
00:36:07,780 --> 00:36:08,260
Sure.

812
00:36:08,260 --> 00:36:09,010
Okay.

813
00:36:09,980 --> 00:36:11,940
Didn't we already withdraw the lawsuit?

814
00:36:13,570 --> 00:36:14,340
Madam,

815
00:36:15,610 --> 00:36:17,900
I've already drafted
the withdrawal application.

816
00:36:18,170 --> 00:36:20,130
Tomorrow, I'll submit it for you.

817
00:36:21,380 --> 00:36:21,900
Madam,

818
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:22,980
Ms. Shu originally

819
00:36:22,980 --> 00:36:24,650
planned to visit you in person today,

820
00:36:24,650 --> 00:36:26,420
but she has an important meeting

821
00:36:26,420 --> 00:36:27,288
and couldn't come.

822
00:36:27,300 --> 00:36:28,780
So, she asked the two of us

823
00:36:28,780 --> 00:36:30,555
to come
and understand the situation first.

824
00:36:31,210 --> 00:36:31,940
Madam,

825
00:36:32,610 --> 00:36:33,460
it's like this.

826
00:36:33,570 --> 00:36:36,490
The next mediation session
has already been scheduled.

827
00:36:36,650 --> 00:36:39,170
Moreover, you've hired
a professional lawyer.

828
00:36:39,530 --> 00:36:41,860
You should be aware of your rights

829
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:44,010
and the possible outcome of this case.

830
00:36:44,530 --> 00:36:46,860
Why did you suddenly decide
to withdraw the case?

831
00:36:47,170 --> 00:36:48,780
Was it your own decision

832
00:36:48,780 --> 00:36:51,090
or was there some unavoidable reason?

833
00:36:51,690 --> 00:36:52,650
Yes, Madam,

834
00:36:52,940 --> 00:36:54,490
now that the judges are here,

835
00:36:54,650 --> 00:36:56,610
if you have any grievances,
please speak freely.

836
00:36:58,050 --> 00:36:59,050
No one will dare

837
00:36:59,050 --> 00:37:01,300
force you to do something
against your will.

838
00:37:05,420 --> 00:37:06,340
Thank you.

839
00:37:06,610 --> 00:37:08,980
Thank you for putting so much effort
into my matter.

840
00:37:10,420 --> 00:37:12,940
Before, I went to Ms. Qin

841
00:37:13,820 --> 00:37:15,940
because I truly couldn't
find my children.

842
00:37:17,780 --> 00:37:18,940
But now,

843
00:37:19,340 --> 00:37:20,980
I have to withdraw the case.

844
00:37:22,210 --> 00:37:23,260
Otherwise,

845
00:37:24,170 --> 00:37:26,130
I won't be able to see my husband.

846
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:29,780
Hasn't your husband already...

847
00:37:29,780 --> 00:37:30,650
Yes.

848
00:37:30,980 --> 00:37:32,860
My husband has passed away.

849
00:37:34,090 --> 00:37:35,380
But while he was alive,

850
00:37:36,050 --> 00:37:37,490
we made a promise.

851
00:37:39,610 --> 00:37:41,940
We'd share one bed in life,
and one grave in death.

852
00:37:42,900 --> 00:37:45,740
He said he was older than me

853
00:37:46,090 --> 00:37:48,300
and not as healthy as me,

854
00:37:49,490 --> 00:37:51,340
so he would likely go first.

855
00:37:51,860 --> 00:37:52,690
He said

856
00:37:53,420 --> 00:37:55,170
after he passed,

857
00:37:56,130 --> 00:37:58,460
he hoped I would live a little longer,

858
00:37:59,380 --> 00:38:00,530
travel around,

859
00:38:01,420 --> 00:38:02,380
see more of the world,

860
00:38:02,460 --> 00:38:04,780
and then choose a place I liked.

861
00:38:05,460 --> 00:38:06,860
And when I pass,

862
00:38:07,570 --> 00:38:08,690
our children should

863
00:38:09,210 --> 00:38:12,460
bury us together.

864
00:38:18,088 --> 00:38:19,511
The day before yesterday...

865
00:38:23,780 --> 00:38:26,380
They said
they would arrange his burial soon.

866
00:38:27,170 --> 00:38:28,050
A few days ago,

867
00:38:28,050 --> 00:38:29,900
I called the children.

868
00:38:30,780 --> 00:38:33,130
I asked them
about the arrangements afterward.

869
00:38:33,900 --> 00:38:34,900
However, they...

870
00:38:36,210 --> 00:38:37,340
They told me

871
00:38:38,210 --> 00:38:40,460
I should forget about taking his ashes.

872
00:38:42,210 --> 00:38:44,130
I know I hurt them.

873
00:38:44,820 --> 00:38:46,340
I shouldn't have gone to you.

874
00:38:46,530 --> 00:38:48,010
I shouldn't have gone to court.

875
00:38:49,570 --> 00:38:50,340
Madam,

876
00:38:51,340 --> 00:38:53,260
so their condition is

877
00:38:53,570 --> 00:38:54,610
that you withdraw the case

878
00:38:54,820 --> 00:38:55,650
in exchange

879
00:38:55,650 --> 00:38:57,650
for taking your husband's ashes?

880
00:38:57,900 --> 00:38:58,980
No, it's not like that.

881
00:39:00,260 --> 00:39:01,170
They said

882
00:39:01,860 --> 00:39:05,050
I secretly kept my husband's assets.

883
00:39:05,900 --> 00:39:07,860
Unless I hand over some hidden savings

884
00:39:07,860 --> 00:39:09,460
and some kind of family heirloom,

885
00:39:09,980 --> 00:39:11,780
they won't give his ashes to me.

886
00:39:12,820 --> 00:39:14,050
But do you know?

887
00:39:14,300 --> 00:39:16,610
From the day I married him,

888
00:39:16,780 --> 00:39:18,570
I never managed
the household for even a day.

889
00:39:18,570 --> 00:39:20,420
I never handled the money.

890
00:39:20,690 --> 00:39:22,820
My husband took care of all finances.

891
00:39:23,690 --> 00:39:24,690
He kept everything

892
00:39:25,010 --> 00:39:26,740
in perfect order.

893
00:39:27,090 --> 00:39:30,170
All I did was cook
and take care of the flowers.

894
00:39:30,530 --> 00:39:32,900
Where would I even find
any hidden savings

895
00:39:32,900 --> 00:39:34,460
or heirloom?

896
00:39:40,610 --> 00:39:42,090
Thinking about it now,

897
00:39:42,244 --> 00:39:43,570
whether they support me or not

898
00:39:44,460 --> 00:39:45,690
doesn't matter much anymore.

899
00:39:51,940 --> 00:39:52,690
Madam,

900
00:39:53,340 --> 00:39:54,860
please don't get too emotional.

901
00:39:55,530 --> 00:39:57,380
Let's talk this through calmly.

902
00:40:08,010 --> 00:40:08,940
Madam,

903
00:40:08,940 --> 00:40:11,050
these are all
your husband's belongings, right?

904
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:13,755
(Bringing good fortune)
Especially this sachet, it smells great.

905
00:40:13,844 --> 00:40:15,490
I can even smell it from here.

906
00:40:16,050 --> 00:40:18,050
He bought this sachet

907
00:40:18,530 --> 00:40:20,610
when we went to Hangzhou
for our 30th anniversary

908
00:40:20,780 --> 00:40:21,940
because he was worried

909
00:40:22,210 --> 00:40:23,260
I'd get carsick.

910
00:40:23,940 --> 00:40:25,090
It really does smell nice.

911
00:40:27,900 --> 00:40:30,010
Madam, this box is beautiful, too.

912
00:40:30,010 --> 00:40:30,980
Are these also...

913
00:40:31,780 --> 00:40:33,530
Madam, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

914
00:40:34,300 --> 00:40:35,210
It's all right.

915
00:40:36,940 --> 00:40:39,260
These are the children's baby teeth.

916
00:40:40,940 --> 00:40:42,940
When I first married into the family,

917
00:40:43,577 --> 00:40:46,210
(My sons Shuo, and Bo)
it was when they lost their baby teeth.

918
00:40:46,650 --> 00:40:47,860
My husband,

919
00:40:48,570 --> 00:40:50,860
being a man, wasn't very careful.

920
00:40:52,300 --> 00:40:53,780
The earlier ones

921
00:40:54,690 --> 00:40:56,490
were never collected.

922
00:40:57,010 --> 00:40:59,170
But when these last few teeth fell out,

923
00:40:59,650 --> 00:41:00,610
it happened

924
00:41:01,300 --> 00:41:02,420
right when I was there,

925
00:41:03,050 --> 00:41:04,980
so I kept them in this box.

926
00:41:11,860 --> 00:41:12,940
In the blink of an eye,

927
00:41:14,420 --> 00:41:16,210
30 years have passed.

928
00:41:24,130 --> 00:41:25,300
Thank you for your trouble.

929
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:30,690
This is outrageous.

930
00:41:31,130 --> 00:41:33,050
How could Ms. Liu's children
behave like this?

931
00:41:33,490 --> 00:41:34,820
Using such despicable methods

932
00:41:34,820 --> 00:41:35,740
to pressure her.

933
00:41:38,130 --> 00:41:39,010
Judge Shen,

934
00:41:39,300 --> 00:41:41,260
does the court have any further plans?

935
00:41:41,844 --> 00:41:44,340
We'll report everything to Ms. Shu
truthfully when we return.

936
00:41:45,010 --> 00:41:46,090
But as you know,

937
00:41:46,177 --> 00:41:47,650
although Ms. Liu withdrew the case

938
00:41:48,090 --> 00:41:49,490
under pressure from her stepsons

939
00:41:49,610 --> 00:41:50,780
and not out of her own will,

940
00:41:50,860 --> 00:41:52,260
their actions

941
00:41:52,380 --> 00:41:54,650
have not crossed legal boundaries.

942
00:41:55,130 --> 00:41:56,170
I understand.

943
00:41:58,130 --> 00:41:59,130
In this situation,

944
00:41:59,130 --> 00:42:00,690
unless you can persuade Ms. Liu

945
00:42:00,690 --> 00:42:02,170
to change her mind about withdrawing,

946
00:42:02,530 --> 00:42:03,650
there's very little

947
00:42:03,740 --> 00:42:04,940
we can do on our side.

948
00:42:05,866 --> 00:42:07,090
That's probably not possible.

949
00:42:07,530 --> 00:42:08,460
Ms. Liu values that urn

950
00:42:08,460 --> 00:42:09,690
more than her own life.

951
00:42:12,610 --> 00:42:13,340
It's all right.

952
00:42:13,444 --> 00:42:14,990
You've already done everything you can.

953
00:42:15,050 --> 00:42:17,380
I'll figure out the rest.

954
00:42:19,530 --> 00:42:20,940
I'll head out first.

955
00:42:28,780 --> 00:42:29,740
Judge Shen,

956
00:42:29,900 --> 00:42:30,940
do you think Mr. Tao

957
00:42:30,940 --> 00:42:32,900
might actually be secretly wealthy,

958
00:42:32,900 --> 00:42:33,940
with some

959
00:42:33,940 --> 00:42:35,340
hidden treasures?

960
00:42:35,488 --> 00:42:36,650
There are quite a few antiques

961
00:42:36,650 --> 00:42:38,130
in Ms. Liu's home.

962
00:42:38,690 --> 00:42:40,050
I don't know much about them,

963
00:42:40,260 --> 00:42:41,570
but what if, like me,

964
00:42:41,570 --> 00:42:43,090
she doesn't recognize their true value?

965
00:42:44,490 --> 00:42:46,610
That might sound a bit rude,

966
00:42:46,820 --> 00:42:47,900
but you get what I mean.

967
00:42:48,690 --> 00:42:50,210
I don't think so.

968
00:42:50,690 --> 00:42:52,900
This is probably just an excuse
from the stepsons

969
00:42:53,170 --> 00:42:54,340
to avoid supporting her.

970
00:42:54,900 --> 00:42:55,740
If Ms. Liu really had

971
00:42:55,740 --> 00:42:57,170
the so-called heirloom

972
00:42:57,340 --> 00:42:58,780
or hidden savings,

973
00:42:59,066 --> 00:43:00,977
and she has no biological children,

974
00:43:01,050 --> 00:43:01,820
whatever she has

975
00:43:01,820 --> 00:43:03,711
would eventually belong to them anyway.

976
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

977
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

978
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

979
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

980
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

981
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

982
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

983
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

984
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

985
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

986
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

987
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

988
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

989
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

990
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

991
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

992
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

993
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

994
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

995
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

996
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

997
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

998
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

999
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1000
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1001
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1002
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1003
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1004
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

1005
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

1006
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1007
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1008
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1009
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

1010
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

1011
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
